            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Writing his wife on Apr. 16, 1865, John Palmer Usher, Secretary of the Interior, describes in detail the death of Abraham Lincoln, which he witnessed, and earlier hints of the assassins&#039; intentions. The letter is a photostat of the original in the Library of Congress.</p>
